I’ve heard parents say a very dangerous statement:  As long as my kid gets what he wants, everything is just fine.  But the minute they’re refused something, all chaos breaks loose.
When I hear that… it tells me that these parents are keeling to their teen’s outbursts.  They’re making a ditch effort to keep peace in the home… but it comes at a high price.  Because placating tantrums only leads to more tantrums… and manipulative behavior that only grows more insidious through the years.
