Are you paying attention to your teen?
I find that many parents want to care for their teen better… but miss one important point of application.  They don’t look below the behavior and personality traits on the surface.
By the time you’ve had fifteen or sixteen years with a child, it’s easy to assume you know him well.  But now’s not the time to slack off in your relationship!  Dig deeper in your conversations… get to know your daughter as if you’d just met.  She’s growing and changing more than you can imagine… and you may find a depth and beauty below the surface that you’ve never seen before.
There’s never been a better time to pay attention to your teen… than right now!
 
