When it comes to teens, what you see is not always what you get.  What may look like uncontrolled rebellion to a parent, may be nothing more than misplaced desire for independence in the teen.  Or… what comes across as an angry kid… may expose some of your own weaknesses!
It’s not always easy to tell the difference, however.  So that’s where you and I need to do some digging.  Look behind the behavior.  Ask some questions.  Wait for answers.
