I don’t know about you … but with a smart phone and a laptop, I’m virtually online all day long!
Just as adults like instant access to the Internet, our kids have grown to demand it, too.  But as parents … how do we let our kids use this great resource without abusing it?  How do we effectively balance a teen’s privacy while protecting them from dangerous world online?
Well, let your son or daughter know that you respect them enough to occasionally dig into their personal online activity … in order to protect them from danger.  Don’t allow them to have free reign on the worldwide web.
Teach your kids that respect and safety go hand in hand.
 
